text.tspan: Use this layer to add blueprints of your
building or other drawing aids.
This layer will be ignored hy the
floorplan compiler.
Rules for Drawing Floor Plans
1. Anything outside the drawing area will be ignored by the
floorplan compiler. The drawing area may have a size of
128x64 or 256x128 pixels.
2. Everything should be pixel-aligned.
- Big walls (2 pixels wide): align lines to full pixels.
- Normal/inner walls: Align lines to half pixels
3. Draw all static elements in layer 'building'.
- Statics must be grey. They will be rendered as drawn.
4. Draw all dynamic elements (yellow) to layer 'gadgets'.
- All gadgets must be pixel-aligned, may be rotated
in 90 steps and flipped, but must not be resized
with the following exceptions:
a) Icons ("lock", "motion", "mail") can be scaled,
but only by a factor of 1, 2 or 4. If the factor
is >= 2 or the drawing area has a size of 128x64
pixels, they are shown in the mini view.
b) Shades can be stretched along the wall side
to match the window width.
5. Layer 'helper' can contain helper material (e.g.
blueprints of the building). This will be invisible.
6. Never change or re-arrange layers! The Home2Ls assume
that layer 'building' has ID 'layer1' and layer 'gadgets'
has ID 'layer2'.
Anything outside the drawing area will be ignored by the
floorplan compiler.
The icons below serve as templates for the Home2L build system
and can safely be removed in the installation.
